Chicken teriyaki buns, scrumptious.

My go-to place in my neighborhood for dumplings! The staff is very friendly and the owners are always there to make you feel welcome. We always buy a bag of dumplings and store them in the freezer. Moreover, they have a great selection of alcoholic and non-alcoholic drinks and at the same time a matcha ice cream! Definitely ask for a chili-oil to go with your dumplings. I will eat all the dumplings you have, can't get enough of them!
Everything is good especially street noodles and mapo tofu. This place is also really kind to people in the neighborhood. Also good beer selection.
I love this place. Everything is delicious and always such a warm vibe!
The sesame noodles were delicious and the staff was so so nice - went out of their way to help me with my order. This will definitely be a repeat spot.
A cool aesthetic with eclectic drink and tasty noodily bites.  Always worth hopping off the G train to stop in.
super

One of the best places I've eaten in New York. Their kimchi is amazing. The dumplings are ok, but the Soba are the best dish they have :) Would love to go there again soon!
This is the box they use to put my food. I didn’t realize it until I reach to the end. I can’t imagine how many plastic particles I just ate.
Small chinese gem in Clinton hill. Great tea and noodles

Took us a while to come back here, even though it's right next to our place... Fantastic noodle soups, dumplings and chive pancakes. Lots of food for a very reasonable price. Many options of beer, sake and Asian teas. The food does take a while to come out, so don't go in a hurry!
Food is good here and hits the spot but not quite my favourite, also I find that their tapioca is always overcooked and mushy.

LOVE this place. Have only gotten takeout and it’s always been delicious (sometimes takes a bit but is always worth it). Make sure to try the vegetable dumplings, sesame noodles, or mapo tofu. Highly recommend stopping by if you’re in the area!

Love the food and the vibes here.

The best dumplings and buns I've had in so long, and a tasty kimchi. Everything was super fresh, and the homemade chili oil, the stuff of gods. The staff is crazy friendly, its a cute place with tons of seating, big communal tables. I will have to come back and work my way through the rest of the menu!
Coffee shop + asian cuisine. Food is good. Opens a little bit later than listed.
Very good vegan dumplings !!!. The edamame dumplings were really tasty.  It's a blend of Asian food and cafe.  The Asian food is tasty.
Once again I work with postmates so i really don't know this place but if I ever come here again It will make me change what I really recommend of this place. Do you know what I'm saying?

Love love the decor and vibes of this place.  Great bubble tea too!  Make sure to try it hot 🙂
Top notch Asian food and coffee in Clinton Hill. Simple and stylish decor. Excellent coffee. Try the lemongrass chicken dumplings and the noodles are divine. Nice selection of local and Asian beers.
Great selection of tea, coffee, and Asian cuisine. Highly recommend the noodles.
Good food, chill atmosphere, crayons.
We got the spicy noodle and fried pork and chive dumplings, SO GOOD! It’s such a great little hole in the wall, definitely worth going to and we will be back!

I love this place, the service is awesome, clean, heard the food is really worth it, many people work on their laptops here, it's my favourite coffee shop around, and you can even add bubba. (I only wish they had more view and sun, maybe some plants and cozier sitting options). Still my go-to.

Place looks great and food was looking good. I picked up an order that night. Unfortunately I realized too late they did not give us the right dumplings. But worst, the chicken dumplings were undercooked — still pink inside — what caused food poisoning to my girlfriend and me.
Nice place for shopping, with a lot of stores.
The mapo tofu is a crime against humanity. Not spicy, no ground pork, no Sichuan peppercorn. Inexplicably lots of cabbage.  Please stop making this dish of you make it this poorly.
Good Food just a little expansive
Love this place. Attitude & food always on point

Amazing organic fresh food and homemade beverages with great tasting! Fusion food with very native Sichuan spicy noodles and rices surprised me! Friendly staffs and warm space to enjoy Asian fusion food and beverage!

Really liked the food, space, and vibe. They have a lot of veggie and vegan options but don't sacrifice flavor. It's a nice open space and they have quality crayons and paper out to help entertain little kids.  We had the edamame dumplings, spinach egg dumplings, mapo tofu, and egg burrito. Dumplings we're amazing, tofu was good. Burrito was pretty good but a little overpowered by the hoisin. They also have a great craft beer can/selection that's fairly priced.

Wooowwwww, eat the Sichuan food!! Beer and everything else is great too. Setup as a coffee shop, I honestly just haven’t tried the coffee yet because I’ve been so happy with everything else. This place is great
Friendly staff and a cozy place to get work done

Tucked away casual Japanese fare, exceptional coffee bar, and a broad selection of beers and Japanese drinks from the fridge, as well as dumplings made in-house. The coffee is some of the best in the neighborhood and the food is delicious. Such sweet staff members.

Good dumplings. Beer selection is unique and great
Nice & cozy dinning area, it's really good to calm your soul and body. Free WiFi. Good service to Customer and the best dumpling in that area.
I like the food and vibe here.

Not super busy. Ok food. I'd eat there again bit wouldn't be excited about it.
Good coffee. Not crowded
Best Taiwanese performance artist boss with best Asian food.

I don't know what happened to their minced pork rice. I came here more than five times and always order the same dish in two years. Every time I came this dish changed quite a lot. The cabbage is totally disappeared, and the egg seems doesn't have enough time to stew, and the pork is SOOOO DRY!!!

Friendly, chill caferestaurant. The food is great however over priced but I'm assuming because they use quality ingredients (I would hope).I recommend the dumplings, rice bowls,and croissants. My only real issue is the chairs for the most part are uncomfortable 😑 but still its worth the visit. I use to sit here and write music def gonna be apart of a good memory when I blow up.
Better than a cafe.

Very warm atmosphere. Nice variety of food and delicious! We had the dumplings and scallion pancakes they were very good! Great neighborhood place to go to! Highly recommend! We’ll definitely be back!!!!!!
Yum. Homemade pork chive dumplings are delicious. I will be back .... A lot Haha

The Market (372 Lafayette) is a local Clinton Hill favorite.  They make some of the best coffee in the area. They also make homemade dumplings and serve craft beer. They have free-wifi and it's a comfortable place to hang.

Definitely good for a quick bite and the staffs are nice. The serving speed really depends, most of the time you have to be patient. Though it's good to have Taiwanese food in clinton hill neighborhood, it's not very authentic..
Great cold brew and lovely atmosphere.
Pricy and the food is average. Quality of food here has dropped in recent months after they changed chefs. Good milk teas though.
Great space with good service & music. Dough on the dumplings are too think for my liking and a bit overpriced, but otherwise good.
Good place for coffee or lunch. Not the cheapest, but worth the money.
Terrible service. Took 45 minutes to make one noodle dish and were completely unapologetic. Avoid this place.
Great place.

The Matcha here is thick and rich... soy milk frothed to perfection, of course, with love. Tried the kimchi rice bowl today and could not have enjoyed it more. Seaweed salad and edammae fresh with perfect ratio of kimchi to rice. Polished it off... not to mention the joyful energy and natural light. Could hang here all day 💙

Favorite coffee shop in an area filled with them. They serve grumpy beans coffee. A major bonus is the food. The menu is always changing and they're always adding new stuff and it's all great especially the dumplings. Service on the food can be kinda slow though.
Great food and coffee at a reasonable price.
Average food at inflated prices. You're way better off heading to any off the plethora of China towns in NYC and eating dumplings/noodles there, or in Prospect Heights, or Williamsburg, or...

They have really great dumplings, a nice beer selection, and great ice cream.
This is a nice place to sit and read. Really good Unagi Don.
Great dumplings and some of the (good) beers are just $2! Try the rice beer also.
Great coffee spot. I learned so muchabout the brewing and the types of coffee from their knowledgeable staff. Off the beaten path but worth seeking out.
Health aid kombucha for face market value is enough to bring me in.  The food and handmade dumplings are good albeit a little overpriced.
Vegan dumplings are AMAZING!!!!
Perfect place for a quiet coffee. Not crowded, modern interior, good coffee, nice people. There are also a lot of fresh produce in huge fridges.
Casual, and friendly ! Love it
Good food - rude, rude customer service .
Always wonderful food, obviously made with care and love. Very nice people who own the market. Very relaxing atmosphere and delicious food and drink.

Barista guy was too tough or cool to deliver basic customer service. The environment was pleasant enough but reminded me of a tech startup open office. I got a rice bowl, seaweed salad and a macha latte. It was all fine but nothing special. Throwing the garbage away was like completing some kind of cognitive assessment: Five bins plus trash to consider as you decide what to do with each thing on the tray. Pretty lousy experience, honestly.

The owner of this place is terrible. Yelled at customers because they didn't spend enough money for their overpriced food. It's not like the place is full with customers and we did not affect their business. We did not want any trouble so we ordered a cup of coffee at the beginning. He was like "you two buy something now or get out".  That's not how you treat a paying customer, its just bad business. Don't go there unless you are willing to speed "enough money".

A great place to have coffee or lunch. They have delicious dumplings. the place is spacious, clean, wonderful people, and great music.
Spotted this place and thought I'd give it a try. The asian food is simple but tasty. Great place for a quick bite.

Favorite new morning coffee spot. The baristas are really friendly and competent. Modest selection of baked goods. Specialty is the homemade gua bao,  a Chinese dumpling of sorts with pork belly and cucumber. Delicious!
